<recipe>
<title>
PB&J Cap’n Crunch Treats
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 5 minutes
COOK TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 15 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
SERVINGS: 9
</details>
<ingredients>
2 T . butter
3/4 c . peanut butter (creamy or crunchy)
4 c . mini marshmallows
Pinch of salt
4 c . Cap’n Crunch
1 c . freeze-dried strawberries , broken into medium-sized pieces
</ingredients>
<instructions>
1. Lightly coat an 8x8-inch pan with cooking spray.
2. In a large saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter together.
3. Stir in marshmallows. Continue cooking (and stirring) until marshmallows are melted and incorporated into peanut butter mixture.
4. Remove the pan from heat, and stir in salt, Cap’n Crunch, and strawberries.
5. Scoop mixture into prepared pan, and gently press it evenly into pan.
6. Let cool to room temperature.
7. Cut into squares to serve.
</instructions>
</recipe>
